<body>
	
<header>
	You should know what you can and can't do during the exam. Look at the questions below, choose YES if you can do this and NO if you can't.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/HF_SP_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"><br/><li id="1">Ask for another topic to discuss. <a id="q1" >YES</a><tab/><a id="q2" >NO</a><br/></li><br/><li id="2">Ask the Examiner his or her opinion of the topic. <a id="q3" >YES</a><tab/><a id="q4" >NO</a><br/></li><br/><li id="3">Ask the Examiner to repeat the question. <a id="q5" >YES</a><tab/><a id="q6" >NO</a><br/></li><br/><li id="4">Ask what the Examiner thought of your performance. <a id="q7" >YES</a><tab/><a id="q8" >NO</a><br/></li><br/><li id="5">Ask for the correct answer to the question. <a id="q9" >YES</a><tab/><a id="q10" >NO</a><br/></li></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left">You can't do that.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left">You must discuss the topic you are given.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left">Examiners want to know your opinion, not give theirs.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left">Examiners should ask the questions, not you.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left">This is fine.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left">Of course you can, so learn a polite way of asking.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left">You will find out when you get your results, no sooner.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left">Examiners can't answer this question, so you shouldn't ask it.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb9">
	<p align="left">There are no correct or wrong answers to questions.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb10">
	<p align="left">It is your opinion that matters and how well you communicate it.</p>
</section>
